    "text":  "Why does a hum hum? AFTERNOON You and most other hummingbirds aren\u0027t very social. You fly alone, eat alone, and build a nest alone. But when you\u0027re with other hummingbirds, you certainly do express yourself! A of hummingbirds can be called a charm. a shimmer. a bouquet. a hover. or a glittering! You communicate by flying. You may do a fast dive. fly in a U shape. or dart around to either attract another hummingbird or signal that they should get out of way. You can chirp. twitter. and sing. Different hummingbirds make different vocal sounds. You protect your territory. If someone dares to get too close to your food or home. you\u0027ll make noise. puff out your chest. raise your feathers. and chase them away If you feel threatened. you might even attack them with your bill. Because doesnt know he words! Rivoli\u0027s Hummingbird",
